{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GshuuDvYCwourPjJgPDieJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 0.5.2: Stream Event Parser\n     2→\n     3→Status: in-progress\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want a stream event parser that extracts tool calls and text from NDJSON events,\n     9→so that the renderer has structured data to display.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→1. **Given** `content_block_start` with `tool_use`, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'tool-start', name: 'Bash', id: 'toolu_xxx' }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→2. **Given** `content_block_delta` with `input_json_delta`, **When** parsed, **Then** accumulates tool input and emits `{ type: 'tool-input', partial: '...' }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→3. **Given** `content_block_stop` after a tool, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'tool-complete' }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→4. **Given** `content_block_delta` with `text_delta`, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'text', text: '...' }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→5. **Given** `system/api_retry`, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'retry', attempt: N, delay: ms }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→6. **Given** `result` event, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'result', cost: N, sessionId: '...' }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→\n    20→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    21→\n    22→- [ ] Task 1: Define typed event discriminated union (AC: #1-#6)\n    23→  - [ ] Create `StreamEvent` discriminated union type with `type` field as discriminant\n    24→  - [ ] Define `ToolStartEvent`, `ToolInputEvent`, `ToolCompleteEvent`, `TextEvent`, `RetryEvent`, `ResultEvent`, `UnknownEvent`\n    25→  - [ ] Export all event types from the module\n    26→- [ ] Task 2: Implement `parseStreamLine()` function (AC: #1-#6)\n    27→  - [ ] Accept a single NDJSON line as string input\n    28→  - [ ] Parse JSON, return `null` for invalid JSON or unrecognized events\n    29→  - [ ] Handle `stream_event` wrapper type with inner API event types\n    30→  - [ ] Handle `content_block_start` with `tool_use` content block (AC: #1)\n    31→  - [ ] Handle `content_block_delta` with `input_json_delta` delta type (AC: #2)\n    32→  - [ ] Handle `content_block_delta` with `text_delta` delta type (AC: #4)\n    33→  - [ ] Handle `content_block_stop` (AC: #3)\n    34→  - [ ] Handle `system` type with `api_retry` subtype (AC: #5)\n    35→  - [ ] Handle `result` type (AC: #6)\n    36→  - [ ] Return `null` for events we don't need (message_start, message_stop, message_delta)\n    37→- [ ] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#6)\n    38→  - [ ] Test tool-start extraction from content_block_start\n    39→  - [ ] Test tool-input extraction from input_json_delta\n    40→  - [ ] Test tool-complete extraction from content_block_stop\n    41→  - [ ] Test text extraction from text_delta\n    42→  - [ ] Test retry extraction from system/api_retry\n    43→  - [ ] Test result extraction from result event\n    44→  - [ ] Test invalid JSON returns null\n    45→  - [ ] Test unrecognized event types return null\n    46→  - [ ] Test empty/whitespace lines return null\n    47→\n    48→## Dev Notes\n    49→\n    50→### Current State -- What Exists\n    51→\n    52→**Story 0.5.1 (done)** switched ralph's Claude driver to `--output-format stream-json --verbose --include-partial-messages`. Claude now emits NDJSON (one JSON object per line) during execution. This story provides the TypeScript parser that converts those raw NDJSON lines into typed event objects.\n    53→\n    54→### Key Files to Read (do NOT modify)\n    55→\n    56→- `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/research/technical-stream-json-terminal-rendering-research-2026-03-19.md` -- stream-json event format reference\n    57→- `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver.md` -- predecessor story context\n    58→- `ralph/drivers/claude-code.sh` -- driver with `driver_stream_filter()` jq reference (lines 151-166)\n    59→\n    60→### Key Files to Create\n    61→\n    62→- `src/lib/stream-parser.ts` -- the parser module\n    63→- `src/lib/__tests__/stream-parser.test.ts` -- unit tests\n    64→\n    65→### stream-json Event Format (Quick Reference)\n    66→\n    67→Each stdout line is a JSON object. The parser handles these:\n    68→\n    69→| Wrapper type | Inner event type | Parser output |\n    70→|:------------|:----------------|:-------------|\n    71→| `stream_event` | `content_block_start` (tool_use) | `{ type: 'tool-start', name, id }` |\n    72→| `stream_event` | `content_block_delta` (input_json_delta) | `{ type: 'tool-input', partial }` |\n    73→| `stream_event` | `content_block_delta` (text_delta) | `{ type: 'text', text }` |\n    74→| `stream_event` | `content_block_stop` | `{ type: 'tool-complete' }` |\n    75→| `system` | `api_retry` | `{ type: 'retry', attempt, delay }` |\n    76→| `result` | -- | `{ type: 'result', cost, sessionId }` |\n    77→\n    78→Events we skip (return null): `message_start`, `message_stop`, `message_delta`, `ping`.\n    79→\n    80→### Design Decisions\n    81→\n    82→1. **Stateless per-line** -- the parser does not accumulate state. Each line in, one event out. Accumulation (e.g., building full tool input from deltas) is the caller/renderer's responsibility.\n    83→2. **Returns null for unrecognized events** -- not an error. The stream contains many event types we don't care about.\n    84→3. **Placed in `src/lib/`** -- it's a utility library, not a module with state or side effects.\n    85→4. **Discriminated union** -- follows the project's `Result<T>` pattern of using a `type` field as discriminant for exhaustive matching.\n    86→\n    87→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n    88→\n    89→- No terminal rendering -- that's Story 0.5.3 (Ink renderer)\n    90→- No integration with ralph -- that's Story 0.5.4\n    91→- No state accumulation -- caller's responsibility\n    92→- No changes to existing files\n    93→\n    94→### References\n    95→\n    96→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 0.5.2] -- acceptance criteria and user story\n    97→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/research/technical-stream-json-terminal-rendering-research-2026-03-19.md] -- stream-json format, event types\n    98→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver.md] -- predecessor story\n    99→\n   100→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   101→## Verification Requirements\n   102→\n   103→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-2-stream-event-parser.proof.md`)\n   104→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   105→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   106→\n   107→## Documentation Requirements\n   108→\n   109→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   110→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-2-stream-event-parser.md`\n   111→\n   112→## Testing Requirements\n   113→\n   114→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   115→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   116→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   117→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   118→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3302fb5a-267f-479c-8444-7f3205e5b9bb","uuid":"7e6c3c51-8f27-4ffa-945b-5bb98857e524","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:29:30.729Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/0-5-2-stream-event-parser.md","content":"# Story 0.5.2: Stream Event Parser\n\nStatus: in-progress\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want a stream event parser that extracts tool calls and text from NDJSON events,\nso that the renderer has structured data to display.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** `content_block_start` with `tool_use`, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'tool-start', name: 'Bash', id: 'toolu_xxx' }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n2. **Given** `content_block_delta` with `input_json_delta`, **When** parsed, **Then** accumulates tool input and emits `{ type: 'tool-input', partial: '...' }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n3. **Given** `content_block_stop` after a tool, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'tool-complete' }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n4. **Given** `content_block_delta` with `text_delta`, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'text', text: '...' }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n5. **Given** `system/api_retry`, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'retry', attempt: N, delay: ms }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n6. **Given** `result` event, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'result', cost: N, sessionId: '...' }`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Define typed event discriminated union (AC: #1-#6)\n  - [ ] Create `StreamEvent` discriminated union type with `type` field as discriminant\n  - [ ] Define `ToolStartEvent`, `ToolInputEvent`, `ToolCompleteEvent`, `TextEvent`, `RetryEvent`, `ResultEvent`, `UnknownEvent`\n  - [ ] Export all event types from the module\n- [ ] Task 2: Implement `parseStreamLine()` function (AC: #1-#6)\n  - [ ] Accept a single NDJSON line as string input\n  - [ ] Parse JSON, return `null` for invalid JSON or unrecognized events\n  - [ ] Handle `stream_event` wrapper type with inner API event types\n  - [ ] Handle `content_block_start` with `tool_use` content block (AC: #1)\n  - [ ] Handle `content_block_delta` with `input_json_delta` delta type (AC: #2)\n  - [ ] Handle `content_block_delta` with `text_delta` delta type (AC: #4)\n  - [ ] Handle `content_block_stop` (AC: #3)\n  - [ ] Handle `system` type with `api_retry` subtype (AC: #5)\n  - [ ] Handle `result` type (AC: #6)\n  - [ ] Return `null` for events we don't need (message_start, message_stop, message_delta)\n- [ ] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#6)\n  - [ ] Test tool-start extraction from content_block_start\n  - [ ] Test tool-input extraction from input_json_delta\n  - [ ] Test tool-complete extraction from content_block_stop\n  - [ ] Test text extraction from text_delta\n  - [ ] Test retry extraction from system/api_retry\n  - [ ] Test result extraction from result event\n  - [ ] Test invalid JSON returns null\n  - [ ] Test unrecognized event types return null\n  - [ ] Test empty/whitespace lines return null\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Current State -- What Exists\n\n**Story 0.5.1 (done)** switched ralph's Claude driver to `--output-format stream-json --verbose --include-partial-messages`. Claude now emits NDJSON (one JSON object per line) during execution. This story provides the TypeScript parser that converts those raw NDJSON lines into typed event objects.\n\n### Key Files to Read (do NOT modify)\n\n- `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/research/technical-stream-json-terminal-rendering-research-2026-03-19.md` -- stream-json event format reference\n- `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver.md` -- predecessor story context\n- `ralph/drivers/claude-code.sh` -- driver with `driver_stream_filter()` jq reference (lines 151-166)\n\n### Key Files to Create\n\n- `src/lib/stream-parser.ts` -- the parser module\n- `src/lib/__tests__/stream-parser.test.ts` -- unit tests\n\n### stream-json Event Format (Quick Reference)\n\nEach stdout line is a JSON object. The parser handles these:\n\n| Wrapper type | Inner event type | Parser output |\n|:------------|:----------------|:-------------|\n| `stream_event` | `content_block_start` (tool_use) | `{ type: 'tool-start', name, id }` |\n| `stream_event` | `content_block_delta` (input_json_delta) | `{ type: 'tool-input', partial }` |\n| `stream_event` | `content_block_delta` (text_delta) | `{ type: 'text', text }` |\n| `stream_event` | `content_block_stop` | `{ type: 'tool-complete' }` |\n| `system` | `api_retry` | `{ type: 'retry', attempt, delay }` |\n| `result` | -- | `{ type: 'result', cost, sessionId }` |\n\nEvents we skip (return null): `message_start`, `message_stop`, `message_delta`, `ping`.\n\n### Design Decisions\n\n1. **Stateless per-line** -- the parser does not accumulate state. Each line in, one event out. Accumulation (e.g., building full tool input from deltas) is the caller/renderer's responsibility.\n2. **Returns null for unrecognized events** -- not an error. The stream contains many event types we don't care about.\n3. **Placed in `src/lib/`** -- it's a utility library, not a module with state or side effects.\n4. **Discriminated union** -- follows the project's `Result<T>` pattern of using a `type` field as discriminant for exhaustive matching.\n\n### What This Story Does NOT Include\n\n- No terminal rendering -- that's Story 0.5.3 (Ink renderer)\n- No integration with ralph -- that's Story 0.5.4\n- No state accumulation -- caller's responsibility\n- No changes to existing files\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 0.5.2] -- acceptance criteria and user story\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/research/technical-stream-json-terminal-rendering-research-2026-03-19.md] -- stream-json format, event types\n- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver.md] -- predecessor story\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-2-stream-event-parser.proof.md`)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-2-stream-event-parser.md`\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n","numLines":118,"startLine":1,"totalLines":118}}}
