{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015z6BVFe2dWJau6JpWdf8Ze","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The stream parser is used by the run command and ink-renderer. It's not exported from the main index.ts, so the verifier can't access it directly as a module. But it IS used by `codeharness run` which is the CLI command. \n\nHowever, verifying the parser's behavior via the CLI would mean running `codeharness run` and checking stream output — which requires an actual Claude session. That's expensive and complex.\n\nThis story is a pure internal library — it defines types and a parser function. All ACs test the parser function's behavior with specific inputs. This is fundamentally unit-testable. Running black-box Docker verification for a parser function makes little sense, but the harness-run process says \"If no tag exists, black-box is used.\"\n\n\nI'll just run the verifier and have it test the parser by using Node to import the built module directly and call the parseStreamLine function. Let me verify that the stream-parser gets bundled into the dist directory.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":314,"cache_read_input_tokens":49303,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":314},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3302fb5a-267f-479c-8444-7f3205e5b9bb","uuid":"24561b34-d7c2-4d4a-a6da-3e24b00b5f1c"}
