{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011ohxVSt43AbkaZDqYukGni","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/epic-0-5-retrospective.md`.\n\nThe epic delivered a clean four-layer pipeline (transport, parsing, rendering, integration) across 4 stories with 2728 tests passing, zero failures, and 95%+ coverage. Key wins: layered architecture held, NFR9 forced good extraction, code review caught real bugs. Key concerns: verification tooling friction (0-5-2 was painful), unauthorized epic insertion, and no E2E integration test for the full pipeline.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Epic-level problems:**\n- **Verification tooling is hostile to internal library code.** Story 0-5-2 (pure function, zero side effects) required workarounds for tree-shaking, missing verification-tier tags, a verify command presentation bug, and a pre-commit gate override. This pattern will repeat for any story producing internal-only library functions.\n- **Story status desynchronization.** Multiple stories had mismatched statuses between `sprint-status.yaml` and their `.md` files. No single source of truth exists.\n- **Epic scope was injected without process.** A subagent added Epic 0.5 to sprint-status.yaml during a Story 2-1 create-story phase, bypassing the sprint change proposal mechanism.\n\n**Stories harder than expected:**\n- **0-5-2 (Stream Event Parser):** Implementation was trivial (stateless parser). Verification was the bottleneck — tree-shaking made Docker verification impossible, verify tool reported FAIL on 6/6 pass, pre-commit gate required manual override. Effort ratio was ~20% implementation, ~80% verification ceremony.\n- **0-5-4 (Run Command Integration):** Hit NFR9 limit on `run.ts` (358 lines). Required extracting 6 functions to `run-helpers.ts`. The extraction was net positive but unplanned.\n\n**Action items needing immediate attention:**\n- **A1 (High):** Fix `codeharness verify` FAIL-on-all-pass presentation bug. This has now hit multiple stories and erodes trust in the verification tool.\n- **A2 (High):** Tag stories with `verification-tier` during epic planning, not during verification. Two occurrences of discovering tier mismatch late.\n\n**Process improvements to encode in tooling/config:**\n- Add `verification-tier` as a required field in story template (tooling change, not just documentation).\n- Make `codeharness verify` exit code reflect AC pass/fail only, not metadata completeness (code fix).\n- Add a pre-commit hook or sprint-status linter that rejects unauthorized epic additions by subagents (config change)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aff9577de7ad438fd (use SendMessage with to: 'aff9577de7ad438fd' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46961\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 143873</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3302fb5a-267f-479c-8444-7f3205e5b9bb","uuid":"d8cd5863-e8ea-4bd7-a512-0bfcb27ea604","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:37:41.419Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /retrospective for Epic 0.5 (Stream-JSON Live Activity Display). All stories are complete:\n- 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver: done\n- 0-5-2-stream-event-parser: done\n- 0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer: done\n- 0-5-4-run-command-integration: done\n\nSprint status is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml.\nSession issues log is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md — read it for context on problems encountered.\n\nReview the epic's work, extract lessons learned, and produce the retrospective document. Write it to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/epic-0-5-retrospective.md.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Epic-level problems (recurring patterns across stories, process breakdowns)\n- Stories that were harder than expected and why\n- Action items that need immediate attention vs. backlog\n- Process improvements that should be encoded in tooling/config, not just documented\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"aff9577de7ad438fd","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/epic-0-5-retrospective.md`.\n\nThe epic delivered a clean four-layer pipeline (transport, parsing, rendering, integration) across 4 stories with 2728 tests passing, zero failures, and 95%+ coverage. Key wins: layered architecture held, NFR9 forced good extraction, code review caught real bugs. Key concerns: verification tooling friction (0-5-2 was painful), unauthorized epic insertion, and no E2E integration test for the full pipeline.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Epic-level problems:**\n- **Verification tooling is hostile to internal library code.** Story 0-5-2 (pure function, zero side effects) required workarounds for tree-shaking, missing verification-tier tags, a verify command presentation bug, and a pre-commit gate override. This pattern will repeat for any story producing internal-only library functions.\n- **Story status desynchronization.** Multiple stories had mismatched statuses between `sprint-status.yaml` and their `.md` files. No single source of truth exists.\n- **Epic scope was injected without process.** A subagent added Epic 0.5 to sprint-status.yaml during a Story 2-1 create-story phase, bypassing the sprint change proposal mechanism.\n\n**Stories harder than expected:**\n- **0-5-2 (Stream Event Parser):** Implementation was trivial (stateless parser). Verification was the bottleneck — tree-shaking made Docker verification impossible, verify tool reported FAIL on 6/6 pass, pre-commit gate required manual override. Effort ratio was ~20% implementation, ~80% verification ceremony.\n- **0-5-4 (Run Command Integration):** Hit NFR9 limit on `run.ts` (358 lines). Required extracting 6 functions to `run-helpers.ts`. The extraction was net positive but unplanned.\n\n**Action items needing immediate attention:**\n- **A1 (High):** Fix `codeharness verify` FAIL-on-all-pass presentation bug. This has now hit multiple stories and erodes trust in the verification tool.\n- **A2 (High):** Tag stories with `verification-tier` during epic planning, not during verification. Two occurrences of discovering tier mismatch late.\n\n**Process improvements to encode in tooling/config:**\n- Add `verification-tier` as a required field in story template (tooling change, not just documentation).\n- Make `codeharness verify` exit code reflect AC pass/fail only, not metadata completeness (code fix).\n- Add a pre-commit hook or sprint-status linter that rejects unauthorized epic additions by subagents (config change)."}],"totalDurationMs":143873,"totalTokens":46961,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2856,"cache_read_input_tokens":43464,"output_tokens":640,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2856},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
